      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(dispatch): forward channel-owned progress callbacks in all chat types when verbose is off",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Removes the `chatType === \"direct\"` guard from `shouldAllowQuietDirectNativeProgressCallbacks` (renamed to `shouldAllowQuietChannelOwnedProgressCallbacks`)\n- Channel-owned native progress callbacks (`onToolStart`, `onItemEvent`, `onPlanUpdate`, `onApprovalEvent`, `onCommandOutput`, `onPatchSummary`, `onCompactionStart/End`) are now forwarded in group and channel sessions when `/verbose off` is set\n- Previously, `/verbose off` suppressed all progress callbacks in group sessions while direct sessions continued to relay them\n\n## Context\n\nReported as #87612. In group/channel Discord sessions with `/verbose off`, users see no tool progress — no indication the agent is working. The `chatType === \"direct\"` guard was overly restrictive: message-level tool summary suppression is handled separately and native channel relay hooks should not be gated on chat type.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Updated existing test: changed from asserting callbacks are **not** called to asserting they **are** called with expected payloads in group sessions with verbose off\n- [x] Verified fix on live Discord group channel — tool progress callbacks (Exec, show data, create folder) visible with `/verbose off`\n\nCloses #87612\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
